Adding more good news to that, our paper related to the challenge dataset was also published in the ACM UbiComp/ISWC '20 Confererence [ URL: https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3410530.3414339 ]. This is our (mine and Abir's) first experience with both things; participating in a machine learning challenge and publishing a paper at a conference so we didn't have any expectations. Gladly, things turned out positively for us. 
Thanks a lot to my teammate Abir Azad for the shared experience in exploration and exploitation. Please pray for us so that we can do more of this divide and conquer stuff. 
I would like to convey our special thanks to Lota Maam for taking us in her team and supervising us all the way with every detail starting from the challenge approach to paper writing. 
Also, thanks to everyone who supported and believed in us on the way. â¤
